The user wants to update an existing ClickUp ticket:
"{{ ticket_name }}"

Their change request:
"{{ user_message }}"

Assignable workspace members (JSON; may be empty):
{{ members_json }}

Return a `ClickUpChange` with ONLY the fields the user explicitly asked to change — leave every
other field null:
- `name`: a new title, only if they asked to rename it.
- `priority`: ClickUp scale 1=Urgent, 2=High, 3=Normal, 4=Low — only if they mentioned priority.
- `due_date`: natural language as written (e.g. "18 June 2026", "next Friday") — only if mentioned.
- `assignees`: the member **id**(s) for the people they named — match on username/email, case-
  insensitive; "me"/"myself" → the single member's id when there is exactly one. Only ids that exist
  in the member list. Null if no assignee was requested or none matched.

Never invent members, dates, priorities, or a new name the user didn't ask for.
